Dog Trainer Questionnaire vs Outcome (AD, CD, GD, W)

Marinara Marcato

Introduction

This document tests the hypothesis that there is a difference in behaviours reported in the standardised questionnaire Monash Canine Personality Questionnaire - Revised considering dog’s training outcome.

Data Exploration

Data Analysis

Kruskal-Wallis one-way analysis of variance test was used to investigate whether there was a statistically significant difference between the behaviours reported by Trainers and the Training Outcome of the dogs. The variables that showed p_value < 0.05 are below:

##                  Variable     status_p
## 1  Extraversion.Energetic 2.056045e-02
## 2     Extraversion.Lively 4.494679e-02
## 3  Motivation.Persevering 2.419062e-02
## 4       Training.Biddable 2.935132e-02
## 5       Training.Obedient 3.901517e-02
## 6       Training.Reliable 2.841315e-03
## 7      Training.Trainable 5.089724e-05
## 8  Amicability.Easy.going 4.735295e-03
## 9     Amicability.Frienly 3.321673e-02
## 10    Amicability.Relaxed 9.396549e-03
## 11    Neuroticism.Fearful 4.596204e-03
## 12    Neuroticism.Nervous 1.418074e-02
## 13      Neuroticism.Timid 3.844166e-02
